etymology: Slang term, likely Bekimon/gay slang, using the place name Narvacan (municipality) as a pun for 'naive' or 'walang alam' (ignorant/clueless).

definitions.meaning: Inosente, walang alam, o kulang sa kaalaman tungkol sa isang bagay; ignorante.
Naive, ignorant, or clueless about something.

examples.example: Huwag kang maging narvacan, gurl. Alam ko namang alam mo ang nangyayari!
Don't be naive/clueless (narvacan), girl. I know that you know what's happening!

etymology: Slang term, likely formed from 'negative' with a playful suffix '-tron', possibly influenced by characters like Megatron. Often used humorously.

definitions.meaning: Palaging negatibo ang pananaw o sinasabi.
Having a negative outlook or attitude; pessimistic.

examples.example: Nakaka-bad vibes ang pagiging negatron mo lagi.
Your always being negative (negatron) gives off bad vibes.

definitions.meaning: Kinakabahan o madaling kabahan (karaniwang tumutukoy sa babae).
Nervous or easily made nervous (typically referring to a female).

examples.example: Nerbyosa ako kapag kaharap ko na 'yung taong nagugustuhan ko.
I get nervous (nerbyosa) when I'm facing the person I like.

etymology: Tagalog word describing a nasal manner of speaking, often due to a cleft palate or similar condition.

definitions.meaning: May kapansanan sa pagsasalita kung saan ang tunog ay lumalabas sa ilong; pagsasalitang parang pusa.
Having a nasal speech quality or defect, often associated with conditions like cleft palate.

examples.example: Mahirap intindihin ang sinasabi niya dahil ngongo siya.
It's hard to understand what he's saying because he speaks nasally (ngongo).

definitions.meaning: Isang pamilyar o pinaikling pangalan na ibinibigay sa isang tao; palayaw.
A familiar or shortened name given to a person; a pet name.

examples.example: Anong nickname ang gusto mong itawag ko sa'yo?
What nickname do you want me to call you?

etymology: Standard Tagalog word from 'laga' (to boil), referring to a dish of boiled meat (usually beef or pork) with vegetables.

definitions.meaning: Isang uri ng lutuing Pilipino na binubuo ng pinakuluang karne (baka o baboy) na may mga gulay tulad ng repolyo, patatas, at saging na saba.
A type of Filipino soup consisting of boiled meat (beef or pork) with vegetables like cabbage, potatoes, and plantains.

examples.example: Masarap humigop ng mainit na sabaw ng nilaga kapag malamig ang panahon.
It's nice to sip hot nilaga soup when the weather is cold.

etymology: Tagalog adaptation of Spanish 'seÃ±ora' (madam, Mrs., lady).

definitions.meaning: Magalang na tawag sa isang babaeng may asawa na o may katandaan; ginang. Maaari ring tumukoy sa isang mayamang babae o amo.
A respectful term for a married or older woman; Mrs. or madam. Can also refer to a wealthy woman or female employer (seÃ±ora).

examples.example: Parating galit ang nyora namin sa opisina.
Our female boss (nyora) at the office is always angry.

etymology: Taglish adaptation of English 'overnight', used as a verb.

definitions.meaning: Ang pagtulog o pananatili sa isang lugar sa buong magdamag.
To stay or sleep somewhere for the entire night; stay overnight.

examples.example: Obernait muna tayo rito para 'di na tayo gumising nang maaga bukas.
Let's stay overnight (obernait) here so we don't have to wake up early tomorrow.

etymology: From Spanish 'obra' (work, deed, act). In Tagalog, commonly means masterpiece or work, but also used colloquially for a scheme, trick, or method.

definitions.meaning: Isang paraan, diskarte, pakana, o trick.
A method, scheme, trick, or tactic.
Trabaho, gawa, o likha (lalo na sa sining).
Work, deed, creation, or masterpiece (especially in art).

examples.example: Kapag nangyari 'yan, may obra ka na naman! (Sense: scheme/trick)
If that happens, you have another scheme (obra) again!
Ang Spoliarium ay obra ni Juan Luna. (Sense: masterpiece)
The Spoliarium is the masterpiece (obra) of Juan Luna.

etymology: Slang term, possibly derived from 'tanga' or 'bobo' with playful alteration, origin uncertain.

definitions.meaning: Katangahan o kamangmangan.
Stupidity or foolishness.

examples.example: Oca mo talaga, bhie! Paano mo nalimutan ang ating anniversary?
Your stupidity (Oca mo), babe! How could you forget our anniversary?

etymology: Colloquial contraction or variant of 'eh di' or 'kung gayon' (so, then, if that's the case).

definitions.meaning: Ekspresyong katumbas ng 'eh di' o 'kung gayon'.
Expression equivalent to 'so', 'then', or 'in that case'.

examples.example: Odi sige, umalis ka na nga!
Well then (Odi) fine, just leave!

etymology: Slang term, likely an inversion or playful alteration of 'gago' (stupid, fool).

definitions.meaning: Isang taong tanga, gago, o sira-ulo.
An idiot, fool, or stupid person.

examples.example: Ogags! Hindi mo ba nakikitang ayaw ko sa 'yo?!
Idiot (Ogags)! Can't you see that I don't like you?!

etymology: Bekimon/gay slang, playful combination of names Nadia ComÄƒneci (gymnast) and Ayatollah Khomeini (leader). Association with 'gay sex worker' is typical of creative/obscure Bekimon wordplay.

definitions.meaning: Isang bakla na nagbibigay ng serbisyong sekswal sa kapwa lalaki, karaniwan ay kapalit ng bayad.
A gay man who provides sexual services to other men, usually for payment.

examples.example: Madalas siyang makita sa mga bar na tambayan ng mga Nadia Khomenie.
He's often seen in bars frequented by gay sex workers (Nadia Khomenie).

etymology: Taglish verb combining Tagalog perfective prefix 'na-' and English 'gets' (understands).

definitions.meaning: Naintindihan, naunawaan, o nakuha ang ibig sabihin.
Understood, comprehended, or grasped the meaning.

examples.example: Na-gets mo ba ang ibinilin ko, Inday?
Inday, did you get (na-gets) what I told you?

etymology: Taglish phrase using English 'evacuate' euphemistically for defecation, combined with Tagalog active prefix 'nag-'.

definitions.meaning: Dumumi o tumae.
To defecate.

examples.example: Sira ata tiyan ni Carlos. Ayun, nag-evacuate.
Carlos might have an upset stomach. There, he defecated (nag-evacuate).

etymology: Tagalog idiom literally 'spreading terror/gloom'. Figuratively and humorously used to mean having strong body odor.

definitions.meaning: May masamang amoy sa katawan o may anghit.
To have body odor; to stink.

examples.example: Mahirap lumapit sa kaniya dahil nagkakalat siya ng lagim.
It's hard to get near him, he stinks (nagkakalat ng lagim).

etymology: Tagalog idiom literally 'unfurled the cape'. Figuratively means to reveal one's homosexuality.

definitions.meaning: Umamin o lantaran nang ipinakita ang pagiging homosekswal.
To come out as homosexual.

examples.example: Akalain mo, nagladlad ng kapa si pare! Badet pala siya!
Would you believe it, that dude came out (nagladlad ng kapa)! He's gay!

etymology: Taglish verb combining Tagalog active prefix 'nag-' and English 'landing'.

definitions.meaning: Nahulog o bumagsak mula sa taas.
Fell or dropped from a height.

examples.example: Nag-landing sa putikan ang cellphone ko!
My cellphone fell (nag-landing) into the mud!

etymology: Slang verb derived from 'maalat' (salty), figuratively implying 'salty tears' or bitterness associated with self-pity.

definitions.meaning: Ang pagkaawa sa sarili; pagse-self-pity.
Feeling sorry for oneself; engaging in self-pity.

examples.example: Nagmamaalat ka na agad, 'di mo pa nga alam ang resulta ng job interview mo.
You're already wallowing in self-pity (nagmamaalat), and you don't even know the result of your job interview yet.

etymology: Bekimon/gay slang verb derived from 'maganda' (beautiful), using 'gee' as a playful element.

definitions.meaning: Mag-ayos o magpaganda ng sarili.
To make oneself beautiful or attractive; to doll up.

examples.example: Teka, magmama-gee lang ako bago tayo umalis.
Wait, I'll just pretty myself up (magmama-gee) before we leave.

etymology: Slang phrase, likely Bekimon/gay slang, combining 'tiling' (shriek) and 'kwitis' (skyrocket firecracker). Derogatorily refers to a loud, attention-seeking, or dramatic gay man.

definitions.meaning: Isang bakla na maingay, eskandaloso, agresibo, o mahilig gumawa ng eksena para mapansin.
A loud, obnoxious, aggressive, or dramatic gay man who seeks attention.

examples.example: Nagkalat ang mga nagtitingiling kwitis sa party kagabi.
There were a lot of loud, attention-seeking gay men (nagtitingiling kwitis) at the party last night.

etymology: Taglish verb from English 'spot' + Tagalog affixes 'na- -an' (perfective passive).

definitions.meaning: Nakita o namataan, lalo na ang isang tao o bagay na hindi inaasahan o itinatago.
Spotted or seen, especially a person or thing that was unexpected or hidden.

examples.example: Naispatan ni Sandy ang kaniyang asawa na may kahawak-kamay na babae sa Luneta.
Sandy spotted (naispatan) her husband holding hands with another woman in Luneta.

etymology: Taglish verb phrase: Tagalog prefix 'naka-' + English 'score'. Has multiple colloquial meanings.

definitions.meaning: Nakakuha ng puntos sa isang laro o kompetisyon.
Scored a point or points in a game or competition.
Nakakuha o nakabili ng ipinagbabawal na gamot.
Managed to obtain or buy illegal drugs.
Naging matagumpay sa pang-akit o pakikipagtalik sa isang tao.
Succeeded in attracting or having sexual intercourse with someone.

examples.example: Naka-iskor ng three points si June Mar! (Sense 1)
June Mar scored three points! (Sense 1)
Balita ko naka-iskor na naman daw si Berto ng shabu. (Sense 2)
I heard Berto managed to score some shabu again. (Sense 2)
Ang yabang niya, naka-iskor lang sa chiks kagabi. (Sense 3)
He's so arrogant, just because he scored (had sex) with a girl last night. (Sense 3)

etymology: Colloquial adjective from Tagalog 'bato' (stone) + 'nakaka-' prefix, literally 'causing one to feel like stone'.

definitions.meaning: Nakakainip, nakakasawa, o hindi interesante.
Boring, tedious, or uninteresting.

examples.example: Nakakabato naman ang palabas na 'to. Umuwi na lang tayo.
This show is boring (nakakabato). Let's just go home.

definitions.meaning: Idyoma na nagpapahiwatig ng matinding atraksyon o pagkakilig sa isang lalaki dahil sa kanyang itsura o appeal.
Idiom expressing intense attraction to or excitement over a man due to his looks or appeal; swoon-worthy.

examples.example: Nakakalaglag panty ang tingin ni Nestor sa akin!
The way Nestor looks at me is swoon-worthy (nakakalaglag panty)!

etymology: Bekimon/gay slang adjective derived from 'ligaya' (joy, happiness) + 'nakaka-' prefix.

definitions.meaning: Nakapagbibigay ng ligaya, tuwa, o kasiyahan.
Causing joy or happiness; delightful or enjoyable.

examples.example: Nakakaligelya ang tumulong sa kapwa.
It is delightful/joyful (nakakaligelya) to help others.

definitions.meaning: Nakakabaliw, nakakainis, nakakagulat, o mahirap paniwalaan (dahil sa pagiging sobra o kakatwa).
Maddening, exasperating, shocking, or unbelievable (due to being excessive or strange).

examples.example: Nakakaloka ang traffic sa EDSA!
The traffic on EDSA is maddening (nakakaloka)!

definitions.meaning: Katumbas ng 'nakakaloka'; nakakabaliw, hindi kapani-paniwala, o kakatwa.
Equivalent to 'nakakaloka'; crazy, unbelievable, or weird.

examples.example: Ang saya talaga kausap ang mga badet, nakakalurky!
It's so fun/crazy (nakakalurky) to speak with gays!

etymology: Slang portmanteau combining 'nakakatakot' (scary) and English 'cute'. Used ironically or humorously.

definitions.meaning: Tumutukoy sa itsurang pangit na umaabot sa puntong nakakatakot (ginagamit nang pabiro o mapanlait).
Refers to an appearance that is ugly to the point of being frightening (used humorously or derogatorily).

examples.example: Huwag mong isuot 'yan, magmumukha kang nakakatacute.
Don't wear that, you'll look frighteningly ugly (nakakatacute).

definitions.meaning: Nakasuot ng napakapormal na damit na tila pupunta sa isang burol o lamay, madalas nagpapahiwatig ng pagiging 'overdressed'.
Wearing very formal clothes as if attending a wake or funeral, often implying being overdressed for the occasion.

examples.example: Bakit ka nakapamburol? Sa palengke lang tayo pupunta.
Why are you dressed so formally (nakapamburol)? We're just going to the market.

definitions.meaning: Maglakad o ang paglalakad.
To walk or the act of walking.

examples.example: Tara, nakatching na lang tayo papunta doon.
Come on, let's just walk (nakatching) going there.

definitions.meaning: Isang ekspresyon ng papuri, pagkagulat, o paghanga, na minsan ay may halong pang-aasar o sarkasmo.
An expression of praise, surprise, or admiration, sometimes used teasingly or sarcastically.

examples.example: Naks, bagong gupit, ah!
Wow/Nice (Naks), new haircut, huh!

definitions.meaning: Naloko, nadaya, na-scam, o nalinlang.
Got duped, cheated, scammed, or deceived.

examples.example: Akala ko totoo, nalerke lang pala ako sa modus niya.
I thought it was real, turns out I just got duped (nalerke) by his scheme.

etymology: Bekimon/gay slang expression combining 'naloka' (went crazy) and 'ang beauty ko' (my beauty).

definitions.meaning: Isang ekspresyon ng matinding pagkagulat, pagkabigla, o hindi makapaniwala.
An expression of extreme surprise, shock, or disbelief.

examples.example: Naloka ang beauty ko! Nakapasa si Mira sa bar exam. Abogada na siya!
I was shocked (Naloka ang beauty ko)! Mira passed the bar exam. She's a lawyer now!

definitions.meaning: Sumasang-ayon, pumapayag, o okey sa isang bagay.
Agreeing, consenting, or being okay with something.

examples.example: Namanchi ako na dapat ay taasan pa ang sahod ng mga guro, manunulat, at editor.
I agree (namanchi) that teachers, writers, and editors should be given a salary increase.

etymology: Mild curse word, likely a euphemistic alteration of a stronger Filipino curse like 'puta' or 'putang ina'.

definitions.meaning: Isang banayad na pagmumura o ekspresyon ng pagkadismaya, pagkainis, o pagkagulat.
A mild curse or expression of dismay, annoyance, or surprise.

examples.example: Namputsa, talo na naman ang paborito kong koponan sa basketball!
Damn it (Namputsa), my favorite basketball team lost again!

etymology: Philippine basketball slang for a player who fakes or exaggerates being fouled; origin uncertain.

definitions.meaning: Sa basketbol, isang manlalaro na madalas magpanggap na na-foul (flop) upang makakuha ng tawag mula sa reperi.
In basketball, a player who often pretends to be fouled or exaggerates contact (flops) to deceive the referee.

examples.example: Ayaw ng mga fans kay Player X dahil nana raw ito.
Fans dislike Player X because they say he's a flopper (nana).

etymology: Internet slang contraction and respelling of the Taglish phrase 'sana all' (hope all / wish everyone could).

definitions.meaning: Daglat para sa 'sana all', isang ekspresyon na nagpapahayag ng pag-asam na sana lahat ng tao ay makaranas din ng ipinapakitang magandang kapalaran, bagay, o sitwasyon ng iba.
Abbreviation for 'sana all', an expression expressing a wish that everyone could experience the same good fortune, item, or situation being shown by others.

examples.example: Ang sarap sigurong makatanggap ng regalo ngayong Pasko. Naol!
It must be heartwarming to receive a gift this Christmas. Wish everyone could! (Naol)

etymology: Bekimon/gay slang using the name 'Narcisa' as a substitute for 'nurse'.

definitions.meaning: Isang nars.
A nurse.

examples.example: Sobrang maalaga nung narcisa sa kabilang ward, maganda pa!
The nurse (narcisa) from the other ward is so caring, and pretty too!

etymology: Bekimon/gay slang using the name of actor Nash Aguas ('Aguas' is Spanish for waters) as a substitute for 'tubig' (water).

definitions.meaning: Tubig.
Water.

examples.example: Mag-igib ka nga ng nash aguas sa balon.
Go fetch some water (nash aguas) from the well.

etymology: Slang verb created by inverting the syllables of the Tagalog word 'punas' (wipe).

definitions.meaning: Ang pagpunas o pagpahid (karaniwan sa katawan gamit ang basang bimpo).
To wipe or give a sponge bath.

examples.example: Nilalagnat ako kagabi kaya nag-naspu na lang muna ako.
I had a fever last night so I just gave myself a sponge bath (nag-naspu).

etymology: Figurative slang use of 'nasundot' (got poked/pricked) as a euphemism for 'got pregnant'.

definitions.meaning: Nabuntis.
Got pregnant.

examples.example: Maagang nasundot si Maria kaya hindi na nakapagtapos ng pag-aaral.
Maria got pregnant (nasundot) early, so she wasn't able to finish her studies.

etymology: Slang, likely Bekimon/gay slang, playful alteration or inversion of 'makunat' (stingy).

definitions.meaning: Kuripot o maramot.
Stingy or ungenerous.

examples.example: Guwapo sana si Mike pero sobrang natmaku!
Mike may be handsome but he's so stingy (natmaku)!

etymology: Slang phrase combining 'NAWASA' (former water utility agency) and 'juice'. Humorously refers to tap water.

definitions.meaning: Tubig mula sa gripo.
Tap water.

examples.example: Birthday mo ngayon, eh bakit nawasa juice lang ang handa mo?
It's your birthday but you only have us drink tap water (nawasa juice)?

etymology: Derogatory slang derived from 'Negro' or 'Negrito', referring to dark-skinned people.

definitions.meaning: (Mapanlait) Maitim ang balat.
(Derogatory) Dark-skinned or Black.

examples.example: Hindi maganda ang pagtawag ng 'negi' sa mga taong maitim.
It is not good to call dark-skinned people 'negi'.

etymology: Colloquial expression of dismissal, disbelief, or contempt. Origin uncertain.

definitions.meaning: Isang ekspresyon ng pagtanggi, hindi paniniwala, o pagwawalang-bahala na may halong inis o pangmamaliit.
An expression of denial, disbelief, dismissal, or contempt, often said with annoyance.

examples.example: Sabi niya manlilibre siya? Neknek mo!
He said he'll treat us? Yeah, right! (Neknek mo!)

etymology: Slang term, likely Bekimon/gay slang, origin uncertain.
synonym: man who has sex with gay men

definitions.meaning: Isang lalaki (karaniwang itinuturing na straight) na nakikipagtalik sa mga bakla.
A man (often identifying as straight) who engages in sexual activity with gay men.

examples.example: Maraming nelatch na tumatambay sa mall na iyon.
There are many guys who hook up with gays (nelatch) hanging out at that mall.

definitions.meaning: Nakawin o kunin ang isang bagay nang walang pahintulot.
To steal or take something without permission.

examples.example: Ni-nenok mo na naman ang lapis ko!
You stole (nenok) my pencil again!

etymology: Tagalog adaptation of English 'nerd', often implying social awkwardness.

definitions.meaning: Isang tao na itinuturing na 'nerd' o 'geek', madalas na may konotasyon ng pagiging kakaiba o mahirap makihalubilo.
A person considered a 'nerd' or 'geek', often implying social awkwardness or being strange.

examples.example: Hindi ko type si Ric kasi masyado siyang nerdo.
I don't like Ric 'cause he's too much of a nerd (nerdo).

etymology: Derived from 'langaw' (fly) + affixes, literally 'beflied'. Figurative slang for something unpopular or unsuccessful.

definitions.meaning: Tumutukoy sa isang palabas, kaganapan, o negosyo na hindi naging matagumpay, hindi pinuntahan ng mga tao, o hindi kumita.
Refers to a show, event, or business that was unsuccessful, unpopular, poorly attended, or failed to make a profit; flopped.

examples.example: Naku, nilangaw ang concert niya kagabi.
Oh no, her concert last night flopped (nilangaw).

etymology: Slang phrase combining 'nilasing' (made drunk) and 'hipon' (shrimp; also slang for a person with a good body but unattractive face).
synonym: taking advantage of a drunk attractive person

definitions.meaning: (Mapang-abuso/Mapanglait) Isang tao na 'hipon' (maganda ang katawan ngunit pangit ang mukha) na lasing at maaaring samantalahin; o ang akto ng paglasing sa gayong tao para makatalik.
(Abusive/Derogatory) A drunk person with an attractive body but unattractive face ('hipon') who may be taken advantage of; or the act of getting such a person drunk for sex.

examples.example: Bantayan mo ang kaibigan mong hipon, baka may magsamantala at gawing nilasing na hipon.
Watch over your 'hipon' friend, someone might take advantage and turn her into a 'nilasing na hipon'.

etymology: Bekimon/gay slang combining 'Ninang' (godmother) and celebrity Martha Stewart. Slang for money.

definitions.meaning: Pera o kuwarta.
Money.

examples.example: Ang kapal naman ng sobreng 'yan. Ilang ninang martha stewart kaya ang laman niyan?
That envelope is very thick. How much money (ninang martha stewart) does it contain?

etymology: Slang verb, origin uncertain, possibly Bekimon/gay slang. Means to open one's mouth to speak.

definitions.meaning: Ang pagbuka ng bibig upang magsalita.
To open the mouth to speak.

examples.example: Hindi siya ninyonyobe buong miting.
He didn't open his mouth to speak (ninyonyobe) the entire meeting.

definitions.meaning: Ekspresyong nagsasabing 'walang problema' o 'okey lang'.
An expression meaning 'no problem' or 'it's okay'.

examples.example: No trobol, pare, kahit sa Lunes ka na magbayad ng utang.
No problem (No trobol), man, you can settle your debt on Monday.

etymology: Slang verb for 'to eat', origin uncertain, possibly Bekimon/gay slang related to 'noki'.

definitions.meaning: Kumain.
To eat.

examples.example: Tara, noakis muna tayo bago umuwi.
Come on, let's eat (noakis) first before going home.

etymology: Derogatory slang term for a dark-skinned person, origin uncertain.

definitions.meaning: (Mapanlait) Isang taong maitim ang balat.
(Derogatory) A dark-skinned person.

examples.example: Itigil ang paggamit ng salitang 'nognog' dahil ito ay nakakasakit.
Stop using the word 'nognog' because it is hurtful.

etymology: Slang verb for 'to eat', origin uncertain, possibly Bekimon/gay slang related to 'noakis'.

definitions.meaning: Kumain.
To eat.

examples.example: Noki tayo sa Jollibee mamaya.
Let's eat (noki) at Jollibee later.

etymology: Slang term for 'to drink', possibly from baby talk ('nom nom') or related to 'inom'.

definitions.meaning: Ang pag-inom, lalo na ng alak.
To drink, especially alcohol.

examples.example: Tara, nomo-nomo tayo!
Come on, let's drink (nomo-nomo)!

etymology: Bekimon/gay slang using the name of singer Nonoy ZuÃ±iga as a playful substitute for 'tuli' (circumcised).

definitions.meaning: Tuli; inalisan na ng sobrang balat ang dulo ng ari ng lalaki.
Circumcised.

examples.example: Sinamahan ako ni Lolo sa pagamutan para magpa-nonoy zuÃ±iga.
My grandfather accompanied me to get circumcised (magpa-nonoy zuÃ±iga) at the hospital.

etymology: Slang term for cigarette, possibly referencing actress Nora Aunor or used as a simple code word.

definitions.meaning: Sigarilyo.
Cigarette.

examples.example: Mars, ilibre mo naman ako ng nora, menthol, ha?
Mars, can you buy me a cigarette (nora), the menthol one?

etymology: Bekimon/gay slang using the name of culinary figure Nora Daza as a substitute for 'magluto' (to cook).

definitions.meaning: Magluto ng pagkain.
To cook food.

examples.example: Ikaw na ang mag-Nora Daza ng hapunan natin.
You cook (Nora Daza) our dinner.

etymology: Bekimon/gay slang playing on the term 'noselift' as a substitute for 'knows' or 'alam'.

definitions.meaning: Malaman o maintindihan ang isang bagay.
To know or understand something.

examples.example: Noselift ko na ang mga sikreto mo.
I know (noselift) your secrets already.

etymology: Slang pronoun created by inverting the syllables of the Tagalog question word 'sino' (who).

definitions.meaning: Panghalip na pananong na 'sino'.
Interrogative pronoun 'who'.

examples.example: Nosi ba 'yang kasama mo?
Who (Nosi) is that with you?

etymology: Slang verb for 'to know', origin uncertain, possibly Bekimon/gay slang related to 'noselift'/'knows'.

definitions.meaning: Malaman, matuklasan, o mabatid ang isang bagay.
To know, find out, or discover something.

examples.example: Gusto kong ma-nostra kung sino ang kumuha ng wallet ko.
I want to find out (nostra) who took my wallet.

etymology: Sense 1 from Spanish 'nota' (note). Sense 2 is vulgar slang for penis, origin uncertain.

definitions.meaning: (Sense 1) Simbolo sa musika na kumakatawan sa tunog.
(Sense 1) A symbol in music representing a sound.
(Sense 2, Bulgar) Ari ng lalaki.
(Sense 2, Vulgar) Penis.

examples.example: Hindi ko mabasa ang mga nota sa piyesang ito. (Sense 1)
I can't read the musical notes (nota) in this piece. (Sense 1)
Nagpakita siya ng nota sa chat. (Sense 2)
He showed his penis (nota) in the chat. (Sense 2)

etymology: Bekimon/gay slang, play on 'nota' (slang for penis) + 'Republic'.

definitions.meaning: Slang na tumutukoy sa lugar na maraming lalaki.
Slang term for a place where many men are found.

examples.example: Nakakaloka, nota republic ngayon dito sa basketball court
Nakakaloka, it's nota republic today at the basketball court.

definitions.meaning: Slang para sa grupo ng mga lalaking maskulado.
Slang term for a group of muscular men.
Slang na tawag sa ari ng lalaki.
Slang term for penis.
Slang na nangangahulugang malaman.
Slang term meaning to know.
Baliktad na baybay ng 'Pinoy'; tumutukoy sa Pilipino.
Reversed spelling of 'Pinoy'; refers to a Filipino person.

examples.example: Marami pa ring pasaway na mga noypi
There are still a lot of stubborn noypis.

definitions.meaning: Daglat para sa 'No Permanent Address' (walang permanenteng tirahan).
Abbreviation for 'No Permanent Address'.

usageLabels: potentially humorous due to other meaning (New People's Army)

definitions.meaning: Daglat para sa 'No Strings Attached'; relasyong sekswal na walang commitment.
Abbreviation for 'No Strings Attached'; a sexual relationship without emotional commitment.
Nangangahulugang sukdulan, sobra, o labis.
Meaning extreme, utmost, or excessive.

examples.example: Nuknukan ng kuripot ang boyfriend ko
My boyfriend is nuknukan of stinginess.

definitions.meaning: Eupemismo para sa kerida o kabit.
Euphemism for a mistress.

examples.example: Mas masarap daw magmahal ang mga number 2
They said that number 2 are better lovers.

definitions.meaning: Slang na nangangahulugang mabaho.
Slang term meaning foul-smelling or stinky.
Slang na tawag sa ari ng lalaki.
Slang term for penis.
Slang na nangangahulugang sampalin.
Slang term meaning to slap.

examples.example: Kapag nahuli mo si Jake na may kasamang iba, nyompaloma picasso mo agad silang dalawa
If you see Jake with another woman, then nyompaloma picasso them immediately.

definitions.meaning: Slang na nangangahulugang 'tama' o 'korek'.
Slang term meaning 'correct' or 'right'.

examples.example: Nyo-rek ka, Magda, nuknukan ng yabang si Delfin
You're nyo-rek, Magda, that Delfin is nuknukan of arrogance.

definitions.meaning: Slang na tawag sa barbero o tagapag-ayos ng buhok.
Slang term for a barber or hairdresser.
Slang na tawag sa shorts.
Slang term for shorts.

examples.example: Ang ikli na naman masyado ng nyorts mo, girl!
Your nyorts are too skimpy again, girl!

definitions.meaning: Slang na tawag sa pustiso.
Slang term for dentures.

examples.example: Nahulog ang nyostises niya habang sumasayaw sa Tiktok
His nyostises fell while he was dancing on Tiktok.

definitions.meaning: Slang na tanong, katumbas ng 'Totoo?'.
Slang question equivalent to 'Really?' or 'Is it true?'.
Slang para sa bilang na pito.
Slang for the number seven.
Daglat sa text para sa 'good night'.
Text abbreviation for 'good night'.
Slang na tawag sa bulbol (buhok sa ari).
Slang term for pubic hair.

examples.example: 'Di raw nag-aahit ng nyulbulayners si Lina, ayon sa mahaderang si Berna
Lina allegedly does not shave her nyulbulayners, according to the blabbermouth Berna.

definitions.meaning: Slang na nangangahulugang tanga o wala sa tamang pag-iisip.
Slang meaning stupid, foolish, or crazy.
Walang ngipin sa harap; bungi.
Lacking front teeth; gap-toothed or toothless.

examples.example: Paano ka ba mai-inlab diyan kay Oliver na ngalbu namang tunay?
How would you fall for Oliver who is ngalbu?

definitions.meaning: Hindi makapagsalita dahil sa gulat, paghanga, o pagkalito.
Unable to speak due to shock, amazement, or confusion; speechless.

examples.example: Nganga talaga ako pagkatapos ng ginawa mo. Ang galing mo!
I was left nganga after your performance. You are amazing!

definitions.meaning: Slang na tawag sa kulangot.
Slang term for a booger.

examples.example: May malaking ngangot diyan sa ilong mo, linisan mo nga!
There's a massive ngangot hanging out of your nose, please clean it!

definitions.meaning: Slang na nangangahulugang baliw o wala sa tamang pag-iisip.
Slang term meaning crazy or insane.

examples.example: Walang kabuluhang makipag-away sa kaniya kasi ngaosh iyan. Hindi ka niya pakikinggan
There is no sense arguing with her because she's a ngaosh. She'll never listen to you.

definitions.meaning: Slang na nangangahulugang baliw o siraulo.
Slang term meaning crazy or mentally deranged.
Ang malaswang senyas gamit ang gitnang daliri.
The offensive gesture made by extending the middle finger.

examples.example: Matapos makatanggap ng panlilibak mula sa galit na mga manonood, ang aktor ay kusang umalis sa show habang naka-ngarat
After receiving some jeering from a disgruntled crowd, the actor left the show voluntarily with a raised ngarat.

definitions.meaning: Slang na nangangahulugang baliw.
Slang term meaning crazy or insane.
Magsalita nang paulit-ulit at nakakainis.
To talk or complain incessantly and annoyingly; to nag.

examples.example: Huminto lang siya ng kangangawngaw nang sumakit ang tonsil niya
She stopped her ngawngaw when her tonsil got sore.

definitions.meaning: Slang na nangangahulugang lasing.
Slang term meaning drunk.

examples.example: Nakaubos 'yan ng isang kahang beer. Huwag mo nang hayaang magmaneho, nge-e na 'yan
He was able to finish one case of beer. Don't let him drive, he's nge-e.

definitions.meaning: Slang na nangangahulugang pangit.
Slang term meaning ugly.

examples.example: Naiinis akong makita kang hinahalikan ang ngetpa na 'yon!
I hate to see you kiss that ngetpa!

definitions.meaning: Slang (mapanlait) para sa pangit na mukha.
Slang (derogatory) term for an ugly face.

examples.example: Ang mga ngetpadudel at manlolokong tulad mo ay nababagay sa zoo!
Ngetpadudels and cheaters like you belong to the zoo!

definitions.meaning: Slang na tawag sa tagasumbong o tsismoso/a.
Slang term for an informer or gossiper.

examples.example: Si Merlinda ang nguso ng isyu na 'yan. Madalas niyang tinitipon ang mga malalapit niyang kaibigan sa mga handaan para mapagtsismisan ang mga taong kinaiinisan at hindi niya gusto

examples.meaning: Merlinda is the nguso of that issue. She often gathers her close friends for parties to gossip about other people she hates or dislikes.

definitions.meaning: Slang na tawag sa tagasumbong o tsismoso/a.
Slang term for an informer or gossiper.

examples.example: Si Merlinda ang nguso ng isyu na 'yan. Madalas niyang tinitipon ang mga malalapit niyang kaibigan sa mga handaan para mapagtsismisan ang mga taong kinaiinisan at hindi niya gusto

examples.meaning: Merlinda is the nguso of that issue. She often gathers her close friends for parties to gossip about other people she hates or dislikes.

definitions.meaning: Isang party kung saan may nagaganap na group sex; orgy.
A party involving group sex; an orgy.
Daglat ng 'overacting'; pagiging maarte o labis ang reaksiyon.
Abbreviation for 'overacting'; being melodramatic or exaggerating.

examples.example: Grabe kung makaiyak si kumare, parang OA na
She was crying loudly, it's almost OA already.

definitions.meaning: Slang na tumutukoy sa lalaking hubo't hubad.
Slang term referring to a naked man.
Slang na tawag sa taong sinungaling o manloloko.
Slang term for a liar or deceiver.

examples.example: Tigilan mo na ako, Barry. Ochosera ka
Stop pestering me, Barry. You're an ochosera.

definitions.meaning: Sobra o labis (lalo na sa palamuti o ayos).
Excessive or overdone (especially regarding decoration or appearance).
Daglat para sa 'overdose'; pagkalango o pagkasawi dahil sa sobrang droga.
Abbreviation for 'overdose'; intoxication or death from excessive drug use.
Slang na nangangahulugang manood.
Slang term meaning to watch.
Slang na nangangahulugang gago, tanga, o bobo.
Slang term meaning stupid, foolish, or idiot.
Ekspresyon ng pagkagulat o pagkamangha.
Expression of surprise or amazement; OMG.

examples.example: Oh my gee! Si Vince at May ay nagkabalikan
Oh my gee! Vince and May got back together.

definitions.meaning: Slang na tawag sa shabu.
Slang term for shabu (methamphetamine).

examples.example: Nagbago na ako. Hindi na ako gumagamit ng oishi
I've changed. I don't use oishi anymore.

definitions.meaning: Slang na nangangahulugang malaki.
Slang term meaning big or large.
Salitang Hapon (madalas mapanlait) para sa bakla.
Japanese word (often derogatory slang) for a gay or effeminate man.
Nangangahulugang mayaman.
Meaning rich or having a lot of money.

examples.example: Bakit okani muchi ka ngayon? Anong raket mo?
Why are you okani muchi today? What's your current racket?

definitions.meaning: Slang na nangangahulugang pagod.
Slang term meaning tired.

examples.example: Pagoda ako dahil sa dami ng trabaho sa opisina
I'm pagoda because I worked on many tasks at the office.

definitions.meaning: Slang na nangangahulugang pagod na pagod.
Slang term meaning very tired or exhausted.
(Sense 1, Slang) Tawag sa kotseng Volkswagen Beetle dahil sa hugis nito.
(Sense 1, Slang) Term for the Volkswagen Beetle car due to its shape.
(Sense 2, Figurative) Sobrang bagal kumilos.
(Sense 2, Figurative) Extremely slow.

examples.example: Para kang pagong kung magtrabaho!
You work like a pagong!

definitions.meaning: Pagkaing tira-tirahan na kinuha mula sa basura, nilinis, at niluto muli.
Leftover food scavenged from trash, cleaned, and recooked.

examples.example: Pagpag ang handa nila sa birthday niya
Pagpag is what they have for his birthday.

definitions.meaning: Pag-aambagan o pagbibigay ng abuloy.
The act of contributing or making a donation.

examples.example: Nagpagulong na si Rowel para sa pagpapagamot sa tatay ni Boyet
Rowel already asked for pagulong for the medication of Boyet's father.

definitions.meaning: Slang para sa baklang nagkukunwari o umaastang tunay na lalaki.
Slang for a gay man pretending to be or acting straight/masculine.
